        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
        <br />
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Effective date: 13/05/2023</p>
        <p>
          Thank you for choosing to use Aladin. We are committed to protecting
          your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information.
          This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal information we
          collect, how we use it, and how we safeguard your data. By accessing
          and using our website, you consent to the practices described in this
          policy.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
        <h4>1.1 Personal Information</h4>
        <p>
          When you create an account on our website, we collect the following
          personal information:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Username: We collect your chosen username, which you use to log in
            to your account and interact with our website.
          </li>
          <li>
            Full Name: We collect your full name to personalize your experience
            and address you properly.
          </li>
          <li>
            Email Address: We collect your email address to send you important
            notifications and updates regarding your account and transactions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Home Address: We collect your home address for shipping purposes,
            ensuring that your purchased items reach you at the correct
            location.
          </li>
          <li>
            Profile Picture: You have the option to upload a profile picture,
            which enhances your account's personalization and allows other users
            to recognize you.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h4>1.2 Business Account Information</h4>
        <p>
          For users with business accounts,or we called it vender accounts, we
          collect the following additional information:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Business Address: We collect the address of your business to
            facilitate commercial transactions and ensure accurate deliveries.
          </li>
          <li>
            Business Name: We collect the name of your business to associate it
            with your account and display it to other users when necessary.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h4>1.3 Shippers' Account Information</h4>
        <p>
          For users who are assigned as shippers, we store the assigned
          distribution hub information to coordinate and track shipments
          effectively.
        </p>
        <h3>2. Use of Information</h3>
        <p>
          We use the collected personal information for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Account Management: We use your personal information to create and
            manage your account, including authentication, profile
            customization, and communication related to your account.
          </li>
          <li>
            Order Processing and Fulfilment: We utilise your personal
            information, such as your home address and business address, to
            process and fulfil your orders accurately and efficiently.
          </li>
          <li>
            Communication: We may use your email address to send you
            notifications about your account activity, order updates, and other
            relevant information.
          </li>
          <li>
            Legal Compliance: We may use and disclose your personal information
            to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or
            governmental requests.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>3. Data Security</h3>
        <p>
          We take the security of your personal information seriously and
          implement reasonable measures to protect it against unauthorised
          access, loss, misuse, or alteration. While we strive to maintain the
          security of your data, please note that no method of transmission over
          the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.
        </p>
        <h3>4. Third-Party Disclosure</h3>
        <p>
          We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personal information to
          outside parties without your consent, except as necessary to provide
          our services or comply with legal obligations. We may engage trusted
          third-party service providers to assist us in operating our website
          and conducting our business, subject to their agreement to maintain
          the confidentiality and security of your information.
        </p>
        <h3>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
        <p>We do not use or store cookies and similar tracking technologies.</p>
        <h3>6. Updates to the Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p>
          We may change this Privacy Policy from time to time andy continuing to
          use our Services after Privacy Policy changes go into effect, you
          agree to be bound by the revised policy.
        </p>
